%N A393967 Decimal expansion of Pi_3, a generalized version of Pi used in squigonometry.
%H A393967 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A393967/b393967.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A393967 Robert D. Poodiack, <a href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/10.4169/math.mag.89.2.92">Squigonometry, Hyperellipses, and Supereggs</a>, Mathematics Magazine, vol. 89, no. 2, 2016, pp. 92-102.
%H A393967 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Squigonometry">Squigonometry</a>.
%F A393967 Equals Gamma(1/3)^3/(sqrt(3)*Pi) = A073005^3/A304656 (see Poodiack, 2016, eq. 7).
%F A393967 Equals 2*Integral_{t=0..1} 1/((1 - t^3)^(2/3)) dt.
%e A393967 3.5332775005708999146273789992968774051437370764051...
%t A393967 First[RealDigits[Gamma[1/3]^3/(Sqrt[3]*Pi), 10, 100]] (* or *)
%t A393967 First[RealDigits[2*Integrate[1/((1 - t^3)^(2/3)), {t, 0, 1}], 10, 100]]
